  {{! too big but thats later }}
  <ul class="sg-colors">
    {{# primary}}
    <li style="background: {{value}};">
      <span
        class="sg-swatch"
        style="background: {{value}}; clip-path: polygon(0 0, 100% 0, 0 100%);"
      ></span>
    {{/primary}}

    {{# contrasts}}
      <span class="sg-label">
        {{name}}
        <br />Hex
        {{value}}
        <br />Contrast
        {{contrast-light}}
        <br />Normal Text AA
        {{light-normal-AA}}
        <br />Normal Text AAA
        {{light-normal-AAA}}
        <br />Large Text AA
        {{light-large-AA}}
        <br />Large Text AAA
        {{light-large-AAA}}
        <br />UI
        {{light-UI}}
      </span>
      {{/contrasts}}
    </li>
  </ul>

<small>{{{meta.description}}}</small>

{{! 
This would be 100x nicer if it was styled or automatic but this is base level

WCAG 2.0 level AA
requires a contrast ratio of at least
4.5:1 for normal text
3:1 for large text.

WCAG 2.1 requires a contrast ratio of at least
3:1 for graphics and user interface components (such as form input borders).

WCAG Level AAA requires a contrast ratio of at least
7:1 for normal text
4.5:1 for large text. 
}}